{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1713,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":21767,"text":"[music by Moby]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":36283,"text":"[Grand Canyon]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":68295,"text":"Narrator: Many of the tests are conducted"},{"time":70490,"text":"while Yves is strapped onto the wing,"},{"time":72300,"text":"because Yves' body\nis an integral part of the aircraft."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75081,"text":"[Wind tunnel tests]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":78343,"text":"Narrator: The wing has no steering\ncontrols, no flaps, no rudder."},{"time":82000,"text":"Yves uses his body to steer the wing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"Stefan Von Bergen: Well, he turns"},{"time":87000,"text":"by just putting his head\non one or the other side."},{"time":89405,"text":"And sometimes he assists that\nwith his hands,"},{"time":92000,"text":"sometimes even with the leg."},{"time":94441,"text":"He's acting as a human\nfuselage, so to say."},{"time":98564,"text":"And that's quite unique."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102160,"text":"Narrator: When he arches his back,\nhe gains altitude."},{"time":114928,"text":"When he pushes his shoulders forward,\nhe goes into a dive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126000,"text":"[Swiss Alps]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":182624,"text":"[Strait of Gibraltar crossing]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":212000,"text":"[English Channel crossing]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":214643,"text":"Commentator One: There he goes."},{"time":216476,"text":"There is Yves Rossy."},{"time":218716,"text":"And I think the wing is open."},{"time":221000,"text":"So our first critical moment, it's open."},{"time":223813,"text":"He is down. Is he flying?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":226832,"text":"Commentator Two:\nIt looks like he's stabilized."},{"time":229050,"text":"He's starting to make his climb."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230599,"text":"Commentator One:\nThere's that 90 degree turn."},{"time":232838,"text":"He's out over the channel."},{"time":235109,"text":"There is Yves Rossy."},{"time":236462,"text":"There is no turning back now."},{"time":238401,"text":"He is over the English Channel\nand under way."},{"time":241456,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":243000,"text":"a historic flight has begun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245620,"text":"[Images: National Geographic]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265165,"text":"Commentator Two:\nAnd as he approaches the ground,"},{"time":267538,"text":"he's going to pull down\non those toggles to flare,"},{"time":269919,"text":"slow himself down just a little bit,"},{"time":272000,"text":"and then come in for a nice landing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281189,"text":"Commentator One: There he is."},{"time":282667,"text":"Yves Rossy has landed in England."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287363,"text":"Bruno Giussani: And now\nhe's in Edinburgh. Yves Rossy!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":290057,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":298903,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":299928,"text":"And his equipment as well."},{"time":301277,"text":"Yves, welcome. It is quite amazing."},{"time":303731,"text":"Those sequences were shot\nover the last three years"},{"time":306982,"text":"in various moments of your activities."},{"time":308866,"text":"And there were many, many others."},{"time":311000,"text":"So it's possible to fly\nalmost like a bird."},{"time":313365,"text":"What is it like to be up there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":315476,"text":"Yves Rossy: It's fun. It's fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317346,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":319377,"text":"I don't have feathers."},{"time":321744,"text":"But I feel like a bird sometimes."},{"time":325067,"text":"It's really an unreal feeling,"},{"time":328410,"text":"because normally you have a big thing,"},{"time":331109,"text":"a plane, around you."},{"time":333000,"text":"And when I strap just this little harness,"},{"time":338550,"text":"this little wing,"},{"time":340130,"text":"I really have the feeling of being a bird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342406,"text":"BG: How did you start to become Jetman?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345162,"text":"YR: It was about 20 years ago,"},{"time":347305,"text":"when I discovered free falling."},{"time":349622,"text":"When you go out of an airplane,\nyou are almost naked."},{"time":354039,"text":"You take a position like that."},{"time":356126,"text":"And especially when you take\na tracking position,"},{"time":359960,"text":"you have the feeling that you are flying."},{"time":363509,"text":"And that's the nearest thing to the dream."},{"time":367694,"text":"You have no machine around you."},{"time":370206,"text":"You are just in the element."},{"time":372000,"text":"It's very short and only in one direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375023,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":376083,"text":"So the idea was, okay,"},{"time":379029,"text":"keep that feeling of freedom,"},{"time":382392,"text":"but change the vector\nand increase the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385789,"text":"BG: So I'm kind of curious,\nwhat's your top speed?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":388761,"text":"YR: It's about 300 km per hour\nbefore looping."},{"time":392000,"text":"That means about 190 miles per hour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395205,"text":"BG: What's the weight\nof the equipment you're carrying?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":397834,"text":"YR: When I exit full of kerosene,"},{"time":400478,"text":"I'm about 55 kilos."},{"time":403235,"text":"I have 55 kilos on my back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405709,"text":"BG: And you're not piloting?"},{"time":407137,"text":"There is no handle, no steering, nothing?"},{"time":409639,"text":"It is purely your body,"},{"time":411201,"text":"and the wings become part\nof the body and vice versa?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":413702,"text":"YR: That's really the goal,"},{"time":415154,"text":"because if you put in steering,"},{"time":417914,"text":"then you reinvent the airplane."},{"time":420579,"text":"And I wanted to keep this\nfreedom of movement."},{"time":425190,"text":"And it's really like the kid\nplaying the airplane."},{"time":428198,"text":"I want to go down like that."},{"time":429872,"text":"And up I climb, I turn."},{"time":432349,"text":"It's really pure flying."},{"time":435722,"text":"It's not steering, it's flight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438599,"text":"BG: What kind of training do you do,\nyou personally, for that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":443614,"text":"YR: Actually, I try to stay just fit."},{"time":447000,"text":"I don't do special physical training."},{"time":452091,"text":"I just try to keep my mobility\nthrough new activities."},{"time":459863,"text":"For example, last winter\nI began with kite surfing."},{"time":464847,"text":"So, new things."},{"time":466000,"text":"So you have to adapt."},{"time":468000,"text":"I'm quite an experienced\nmanager of systems as a pilot,"},{"time":473579,"text":"but this is, really --"},{"time":475000,"text":"You need fluidity,"},{"time":477388,"text":"you need to be agile"},{"time":479880,"text":"and also to adapt really fast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482380,"text":"BG: Somebody in the audience asked me,"},{"time":484214,"text":"\"How does he breathe up there?\""},{"time":486000,"text":"Because you're going fast\nand you're up at 3,000 meters or so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489001,"text":"YR: Okay, up to 3,000 meters,"},{"time":491277,"text":"it's not such a big problem with oxygen."},{"time":494967,"text":"But for example, bikers,"},{"time":497553,"text":"they have the same speed."},{"time":499548,"text":"Just with the helmet, integral helmet,"},{"time":501962,"text":"it's really no problem to breathe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503938,"text":"BG: Describe for me the equipment,\nsince you have it here."},{"time":506729,"text":"So Breitling's four engines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508844,"text":"YR: Yeah, two-meter span."},{"time":511586,"text":"Ultra-stable profile."},{"time":513000,"text":"Four little engines,"},{"time":514865,"text":"22 kilos thrust each,"},{"time":517436,"text":"turbines, working with kerosene."},{"time":520800,"text":"Harness, parachute."},{"time":523682,"text":"My only instruments\nare an altimeter and time."},{"time":526889,"text":"I know I have about eight minutes fuel."},{"time":530560,"text":"So I just check before it's finished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533337,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":536369,"text":"And yeah, that's all."},{"time":538655,"text":"Two parachutes."},{"time":541441,"text":"That means, if I have a problem\nwith the first one I pull,"},{"time":546142,"text":"I still have the possibility\nto open the second one."},{"time":549784,"text":"And this is my life."},{"time":551204,"text":"That's the real important\nthing about safety."},{"time":554807,"text":"I did use that during these last 15 years"},{"time":558403,"text":"about 20 times."},{"time":560266,"text":"Never with that type of wing,\nbut at the beginning."},{"time":563568,"text":"I can release my wing"},{"time":566631,"text":"when I am in a spin or unstable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569781,"text":"BG: We saw the 2009 crossing\nof the Gibraltar Strait"},{"time":572498,"text":"where you lost control"},{"time":574000,"text":"and then you dived down into the clouds"},{"time":576809,"text":"and in the ocean."},{"time":578000,"text":"So that was one of those cases\nwhere you let the wings go, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581821,"text":"YR: Yeah. I did try in the clouds,"},{"time":584270,"text":"but you lose orientation completely."},{"time":587000,"text":"So I did try to take, again,"},{"time":589580,"text":"a climb altitude."},{"time":592532,"text":"I thought, okay, I will go out."},{"time":594604,"text":"But most probably,\nI did something like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597419,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598513,"text":"BG: Something that is not\nvery safe, the image."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"YR: You feel great, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":604069,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":606347,"text":"But you have not the right altitude."},{"time":608810,"text":"So the next thing I saw was just blue."},{"time":611532,"text":"It was the sea."},{"time":613000,"text":"I have also an audible altimeter."},{"time":616010,"text":"So I was at my minimum altitude"},{"time":618336,"text":"in that vector -- fast --"},{"time":621668,"text":"so I pulled that."},{"time":623545,"text":"And then I did open my chute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624967,"text":"BG: So the wings have their own parachute,\nand you have your two parachutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628563,"text":"YR: Exactly. There is a rescue\nparachute for the wing"},{"time":631198,"text":"for two reasons:"},{"time":633000,"text":"so I can repair it afterward"},{"time":634739,"text":"and especially so nobody takes\nthat, just on his head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640109,"text":"BG: I see. Maybe come back here."},{"time":642364,"text":"This is risky stuff indeed."},{"time":644817,"text":"People have died trying\nto do this kind of thing."},{"time":647766,"text":"And you don't look like a crazy guy;\nyou're a Swiss airline pilot,"},{"time":650886,"text":"so you're rather a checklist kind of guy."},{"time":653676,"text":"I assume you have standards."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655470,"text":"YR: Yeah. I have no checklist for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658201,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":659323,"text":"BG: Let's not tell your employer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660998,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":662114,"text":"YR: No, that's really two worlds."},{"time":665686,"text":"Civil aviation is something\nthat we know very well."},{"time":668806,"text":"We have a hundred years of experience."},{"time":671726,"text":"And you can adapt really precisely."},{"time":675984,"text":"With that, I have to adapt\nto something new."},{"time":679000,"text":"That means improvise."},{"time":681000,"text":"So it's really a play\nbetween these two approaches."},{"time":684254,"text":"Something that I know\nvery well, these principles."},{"time":687493,"text":"For example, we have\ntwo engines on an Airbus;"},{"time":690778,"text":"with only one engine, you can fly it."},{"time":693157,"text":"So plan B, always a plan B."},{"time":695768,"text":"In a fighter, you have an ejection seat."},{"time":697698,"text":"That's my ejection seat."},{"time":699749,"text":"So I have the approach\nof a professional pilot"},{"time":702749,"text":"with the respect of a pioneer"},{"time":708018,"text":"in front of Mother Nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710501,"text":"BG: It's well said."},{"time":713000,"text":"What happens if one of the engines stops?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":716144,"text":"YR: I do a roll."},{"time":719797,"text":"And then I stabilize,"},{"time":723105,"text":"and according to my altitude,\nI continue on two or three engines."},{"time":727101,"text":"It's sometimes possible."},{"time":728682,"text":"It's quite complicated to explain,"},{"time":731883,"text":"but according to which regime I was,"},{"time":735277,"text":"I can continue on two"},{"time":737000,"text":"and try to get a nice place to land,\nand then I open my parachute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740643,"text":"BG: So the beginning of the flight"},{"time":742288,"text":"is actually you jump\noff a plane or a helicopter,"},{"time":744684,"text":"and you go on a dive\nand accelerate the engines,"},{"time":747427,"text":"and then you basically take off\nmid-air somewhere."},{"time":750000,"text":"And then the landing, as we have seen,"},{"time":752000,"text":"arriving on this side of the Channel,"},{"time":754866,"text":"is through a parachute."},{"time":756585,"text":"So just as a curiosity,"},{"time":758474,"text":"where did you land when you flew\nover the Grand Canyon?"},{"time":761896,"text":"Did you land on the rim,\ndown at the bottom?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"YR: It was down on the bottom."},{"time":766294,"text":"And I came back afterward\non the sled of the helicopter back."},{"time":770670,"text":"But it was too stony\nand full of cactus on top."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775103,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":776143,"text":"BG: That's exactly\nwhy I asked the question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778309,"text":"YR: And also, the currents\nare quite funny there."},{"time":782158,"text":"There is big thermal activity,"},{"time":784388,"text":"big difference in altitude also."},{"time":786444,"text":"So it was much safer for me\nto land at the bottom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790941,"text":"BG: I think that right now,\nmany people are asking,"},{"time":793718,"text":"\"When are you developing a double-seater"},{"time":795710,"text":"so they can fly with you?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":797000,"text":"YR: I have a standard answer."},{"time":799206,"text":"Have you ever seen tandem birds?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":803204,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":804231,"text":"BG: Perfect answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805396,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":813803,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":815000,"text":"BG: Yves, one last question."},{"time":817721,"text":"What's next for you?\nWhat's next for Jetman?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":820000,"text":"YR: First, to instruct a younger guy."},{"time":824335,"text":"I want to share it,\nto do formation flights."},{"time":827904,"text":"And I plan to start from a cliff,"},{"time":830442,"text":"like catapulted from a cliff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832347,"text":"BG: So instead of jumping\noff a plane, yes?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":834372,"text":"YR: Yes, with the final goal to take off,\nbut with initial speed."},{"time":838605,"text":"Really, I go step by step."},{"time":840636,"text":"It seems a little bit crazy, but it's not."},{"time":843744,"text":"It's possible to start already now,\nit's just too dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847323,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":849307,"text":"Thanks to the increasing technology,\nbetter technology,"},{"time":854719,"text":"it will be safe."},{"time":856026,"text":"And I hope it will be for everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858811,"text":"BG: Yves, thank you very much. Yves Rossy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860837,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}